        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 3:24PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Robinsonville, or 7 miles southeast of Hughes, moving northeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Horseshoe Lake, Pinckney, Lake Cormorant, Eudora, Robinsonville,
Newport, Clack, Trinity, Commerce, Lost Lake, Seyppel, Beck, Bruins,
Glover, Banks, Penton, Bowdre, and Norfolk.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
